            - citation-agot-appendix
        confidence: high
        status: accepted
        notes: "Verified against TWOIAF, The Targaryen Kings section. AGOT Appendix lists '172-184 Aegon IV the Unworthy, eldest son of Viserys'. Source text: WITH HIS FATHER'S death in 172 AC, Aegon, the Fourth of his Name, came at last to the throne that he had coveted as a boy. He had been comely in his youth, skilled with lance and sword, a man who loved to hunt and hawk and dance."
